## 🎯 MITRE ATT\&CK Mapping – SQL Injection

| Technique ID | Technique Name | Tactic | Sub-technique | Description |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| [T1190](https://attack.mitre.org/techniques/T1190/) | **Exploit Public-Facing Application** | Initial Access | — | Adversary exploits a weakness in the web application's SQL query construction to gain access. |
| [T1059](https://attack.mitre.org/techniques/T1059/) | **Command and Scripting Interpreter** | Execution | [T1059.007](https://attack.mitre.org/techniques/T1059/007/) – JavaScript | Attacker may use time-based blind SQLi or stacked queries to execute DB-side commands. |
| [T1005](https://attack.mitre.org/techniques/T1005/) | **Data from Local System** | Collection | — | Attacker reads sensitive data (credentials, PII, tokens) directly from the database. |
| [T1552](https://attack.mitre.org/techniques/T1552/) | **Unsecured Credentials** | Credential Access | [T1552.001](https://attack.mitre.org/techniques/T1552/001/) – Credentials in Files | Database may store plaintext or weakly hashed credentials accessible via SQLi. |
| [T1213](https://attack.mitre.org/techniques/T1213/) | **Data from Information Repositories** | Collection | — | Adversary exfiltrates records from `{{ db_name | default("the targeted database") }}` through the injection vector. |
| [T1565](https://attack.mitre.org/techniques/T1565/) | **Data Manipulation** | Impact | [T1565.001](https://attack.mitre.org/techniques/T1565/001/) – Stored Data Manipulation | Attacker may INSERT, UPDATE, or DELETE records to corrupt or tamper with data. |
| [T1110](https://attack.mitre.org/techniques/T1110/) | **Brute Force** | Credential Access | [T1110.002](https://attack.mitre.org/techniques/T1110/002/) – Password Cracking | Hashes extracted via SQLi may be offline-cracked to gain further access. |
| [T1078](https://attack.mitre.org/techniques/T1078/) | **Valid Accounts** | Persistence, Defense Evasion | — | Credentials stolen from DB may be used to log in as legitimate users. |

> 📖 References: [MITRE ATT&CK – T1190](https://attack.mitre.org/techniques/T1190/) · [OWASP SQLi](https://owasp.org/www-community/attacks/SQL_Injection)

