### SIEM Detection Queries

**Query 1 – SQLi Payload Detection (HTTP params):**
```splunk
index=web-access src_ip="{{ source_ip | default("*") }}"
  uri="{{ target_url | default("*") }}"
  | regex _raw="(?i)(union.*select|'.*or.*'|--|;.*drop|information_schema|sleep\(|benchmark\(|load_file|into.*outfile)"
  | table _time, src_ip, uri, http_method, status, bytes
  | sort - _time
```

**Query 2 – DB Error Spike (Error-Based SQLi):**
```splunk
index=db-errors db_host="{{ db_host | default("*") }}"
  | bin _time span=1m
  | stats count as error_count by _time, db_host, error_code
  | where error_count > 10
  | sort - error_count
```

**Query 3 – Blind SQLi Time-Based Detection:**
```splunk
index=web-access src_ip="{{ source_ip | default("*") }}"
  | eval response_time=tonumber(response_ms)
  | where response_time > 5000 AND uri="{{ target_url | default("*") }}"
  | stats avg(response_time) as avg_ms, max(response_time) as max_ms, count by src_ip, uri
  | sort - max_ms
```

**Query 4 – UNION SELECT Enumeration:**
```splunk
index=waf-logs
  | regex message="(?i)union.*select|information_schema|group_concat"
  | stats count by src_ip, matched_pattern, uri
  | sort - count
```

**Query 5 – Post-Compromise DB Activity:**
```splunk
index=db-audit db_name="{{ db_name | default("*") }}"
  event_type IN ("INSERT", "UPDATE", "DELETE", "DROP", "CREATE")
  | table _time, db_user, event_type, object_name, sql_text, rows_affected
  | where _time > relative_time(now(), "-48h")
  | sort - _time
```

